ted “there are probably more menstruating women in the world than incontinent babies” personal lifeedit valerie hunter gordon was the granddaughter of inventor sebastian ziani de ferranti the founder of british electrical engineering firm ferranti greatgranddaughter of italian classical guitarist and composer marco aurelio zani de ferranti and the sister of basil de ferranti her maternal grandmother juliana scott was a concert pianist valerie married the decorated royal engineer major patrick hunter gordon she died on  october  at the age of  and was survived by six children  grandchildren and  greatgrandchildren referencesedit  a b c d burnside anna  may  meet the scots woman who started a babycare revolution by banishing the drudgery of handwashing diapers the daily record retrieved  october    kellock andrew  october  woman who invented disposable nappies has died aged  at her highland home the press and journal retrieved  october    a b lawson jim  october  scottish inventor of the disposable nappy dies at  wwwscotsmancom the scotsman retrieved  october    a b c paddi pads fleecy disposable soft napkins  mrs valerie huntergordon  va search the collections collectionsvamacuk va museum retrieved  october    a b history paddi retrieved  october    for more information go to httpwwwpaddiorguk  httpwwwbbccoukprogrammesbxdw  valerie de ferranti peeragecom retrieved  october   disposable nappy inventor valerie hunter gordon dies aged  bbc news bbc  october  retrieved  october   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlevaleriehuntergordonoldid categories ferrantiscottish inventors birthswomen inventors deathsscottish people of italian descenthidden categories articles with hcardsplace of birth missing navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store int